    hhs deque info

    Knowledge Base Article - CTAC (Communications Training Analysis Corporation)  
=================================================

Subject: Deque Information

Revision History:
    2015-03-02 09:52:41 - Version 1 created by Bao
    2017-01-16 9:44:51 - Version 1.b Updated for Deque 6.1.4
    2018-09-25 11:55:13 - Version 2 added LDAP settings info
 
Assets:
- hhs-deque-core-01.prod.hhs.local (m4.xlarge)
- hhs-deque-analysis-01.prod.hhs.local (m4.xlarge)
- RDS

UI Login
- hhs-deque-core-01.prod.hhs.local/auth
- hhs-deque-core-01.prod.hhs.local/worldspace (LDAP)

Current Deque version: 6.1.4

Prerequisites
- Packages that need to be installed on the core server: 
   supervisor
   rabbitmq
   After rabbitmq is installed, run the following commands (substitute the password as necessary)
      rabbitmqctl add_vhost /
      rabbitmqctl add_user dqadmin admin
      rabbitmqctl set_user_tags dqadmin administrator
      rabbitmqctl set_permissions -p / dqadmin ".*" ".*" ".*"
   Redis
      Redis vulnerability:
        in /etc/redis/redis.conf, in the requirepass directive, add a password
        in Deque:
         cd /appdata/deque/mounts/config-server 
         vi application.yml
         in the redis section add the following:
               password: <<<< password from above >>>
         
   Mongo
      in /etc/mongo.conf, ensure the following is enabled:
         security:  authorization: enabled
      Mongo password:
         mongodb://username:password@hhs-deque-core-01.stg.hhs.local:27018/deque
      Also need to run some mongo commands to create users and databases (be careful of the copy/paste of quotes/backticks)
         mongo admin --port 27018 --eval "db.createUser({ user: 'mongodeque', pwd: 'Hw6wmaPF2jhqkWDob', roles: [ { role: 'dbOwner', db: 'admin' } ] });"
         mongo deque --port 27018 --eval "db.createUser({ user: 'mongodeque', pwd: 'Hw6wmaPF2jhqkWDob', roles: [ { role: 'dbOwner', db: 'deque' } ] });"
         mongo deque-custom-rules --port 27018 --eval "db.createUser({ user: 'mongodeque', pwd: 'Hw6wmaPF2jhqkWDob', roles: [ { role: 'dbOwner', db:'deque-custom-rules' } ] });"


         ****** TO DO:::: - find out why mongo is not starting using the service. ******
- Packages that need to be installed on the analysis server
   supervisor
   Chrome
      wget -q -O - https://dl-ssl.google.com/linux/linux_signing_key.pub | sudo apt-key add -
      echo "deb [arch=amd64] http://dl.google.com/linux/chrome/deb/ stable main" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/google-chrome.list
      apt-get update
      apt-get install -y google-chrome-stable
  XVFB
      apt-get install -y libgtk-3-dev xvfb
      

- Ports that need to be open from analysis server to core server:
  5672 (rabbitmq)
   6379 (redis)
   8095 (deque application port)
   8761 (deque application port)
   15672 (rabbitmq admin)
   27018 (mongo make sure to point the datadir to /appdata/mongo)


- installer (this is the deque *.run file)
- RDS (if you go MySQL, make sure that you configure the datadir to /appdata/mysql)
    create 2 databases:
       wscomply
       wauth
    create 1 user with access to both databases

============================================================================================================
Running processes on each Deque server. These processes are handled by supervisor
============================================================================================================
Core server
- LoadController
- TaskProcessor
- BrowserHub
- DocumentProcessor
- WorldspaceComply
- WSAuth
- WSWeb (Nginx)

Analysis server
- BrowserService
- WSMgrService



Log files
/appdata/deque/logs
/appdata/deque/tomcat/logs
*Logs must be cleared manually.


============================================================================================================
Contacting Deque support 
Send an email to: help@deque.com
Allowed users to contact Deque support: bnguyen, ktzeng, Alex(HHS), possibly 1 or 2 others.
In the email include
- description of the problem
- version of worldspace (currently 6.1.4
============================================================================================================

Normal order of start process:
- Core Server
  - WSWeb
  - WSAuth
  - WorldspaceComply
  (Pause and wait until UI is up)
  - BrowserHub
  - BrowserService
  To verify processes have started you can tail BrowserService.log and see where it says ‘connected to hub’
  - TaskProcessor
  Tail BrowserService.log and check for ‘firefox running’ message.
  - DocumentProcessor
  - LoadController
  - WSMgrService


============================================================================================================
Troubleshooting
============================================================================================================

If a user reports that the scans appear to be running but not ‘moving’:
Stop scanning services in the following order:
- LoadController
- TaskProcessor
- BrowserHub
- BrowserService

Then start scanning services in the following order:
- BrowserHub
- BrowserService
- TaskProcessor
- DocumentProcessor
- LoadController

- mongo disk space on hhs-deque-core-01.prod.hhs.local
  Mongo database only keeps cached data. This can be dropped at any time. Drop the database with the following command (can be cron'd as necessary):
  /usr/bin/mongo deque --port 27018 --eval "db.dropDatabase()"

- logrotate for /appdata/deque/log
      in /appdata/deque/supervisord
      edit: comply.conf
      add:
         stdout_logfile_backups=x

      then run: (when you run the update command, there's a chance that it'll restart the services, so schedule accordingly)
         supervisorctl reread
         supervisorctl update


- uninstalling deque
   to uninstall deque go into cd /appdata/deque and run the uninstall script. THen remove the contents of /appdata/deque/*



- How to stop all running scans from the database
   1) MySQL queries
      DELETE FROM wscomply.work_queue_item;
      UPDATE wscomply.spider_job SET location = null, status = 'Completed';
      UPDATE wscomply.issue SET marked_for_deletion = 0;
   2) Rabbitmq
      Also need to clear the rabbitmq queues.
      - stop rabbitmq service (/etc/init.d/rabbitmq-server stop)
      - remove contents of /appdata/rabbitmq/mnesia/<hostname>/
      - restart rabbitmq service
      - rerun the rabbitmqctl commands to create the user:
        rabbitmqctl add_user dqadmin deque && rabbitmqctl set_user_tags dqadmin administrator && rabbitmqctl set_permissions -p / dqadmin ".*" ".*" ".*"
      - enable the plugins again
        sudo rabbitmq-plugins enable rabbitmq_management

- Troubleshooting connections to Database
   The database connection strings are stored in 
      /appdata/deque/tmocat/comm/classes/WorldSpaceConfig.groovy
  

- Enabling debug:
  Change 2 files:
  /appdata/deque/mounts/config-server

- Enabling LDAP (ensuring LDAP is used)
  vi /appdata/deque/mounts/config-server/worldspace-core/production/application.yml
  Change:
    useldap=false
  to:
    useldap=true



- Assigning a user as an administrator
1. Connect to the worldspace mysql server, and select the appropriate database.
        use DATABASE_NAME;

Example:
   use wscomply;

2.Find the User ID of the user in question.
        select id,username,email from fireeyesuser whereemail='user_email@domain';

        +----+---------------------------------+-----------------------------------+
        | id   | username                   | email                           |
        +----+---------------------------------+-----------------------------------+
        |  7   |user_email@domain  |user_email@domain    |
        +----+---------------------------------+-----------------------------------+
            A sample user ID

3. Set the user as an administrator, where N in the following query is the user's ID.
        INSERT INTO role_people VALUES((SELECT id FROM role WHERE authority='ROLE_ADMIN'), N);


- To remove admin privileges from a user, use
    UPDATE role_people SET role_id=(SELECT id FROM role WHERE authority='ROLE_USER') WHERE role_id = (select id from role where authority = 'ROLE_ADMIN') AND user_id=N;
- Mass add a user account to all projects as admin
   INSERT INTO fireeyesgroup_fireeyesuser (group_users_id, user_id) SELECT DISTINCT fg.id, (SELECT id FROM fireeyesuser WHERE email='email@domain') FROM fireeyesgroup fg WHERE fg.name='admins';

Updating DNS for Deque
- Keycloak 
In Keycloak, append DNS to comply section > clients


- hhs-deque-core-01.prod.hhs.local
- in deque/common/classes directory
- Edit WorldSpace_config.groovy -> confirm https & URL change
- Edit keycloak.json file -> confirm https://... URL
- deque/components/web/conf.d/*
remove deque-specific ssl cert references

- Mongo issues
   if mongo is failing tail the manager.log: /appdata/deque/logs/manager.log

============================================================================================================
Deque UI Login (need to port to 1password
============================================================================================================
URL: https://deque1.cloud.hhs.gov/keycloak
admin@deque.com
admin

============================================================================================================
Installation issues and workarounds
============================================================================================================
on analysis server, make sure the following is running:

/usr/bin/Xvfb :6 -ac -screen 0 1024x768x16 -fbdir /tmp/
/usr/bin/xterm -display :6 -e ./runBrowserService.sh

- On the analysis server, the installer expects that nginx be installed, even though it only runs on the core server. The directory for nginx may not exist. The installer will eventually timeout. It's probably a good idea to mkdir -p /etc/nginx as a blank directory. 

——————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————
(Deprecated - Firefox is no longer used - chrome is the package that you want to install)
Firefox package version (dpkg -l | grep firefox)
- need to ensure version 45.5.1


============================================================================================================
The /appdata/deque/bin directory
============================================================================================================
This directory is, well, the bin directory.

db_upgrade.sh is often run after an install. 
first_run.sh is run only on a fresh install.


============================================================================================================
Overview of Installation
============================================================================================================


1) download the deque installer (both analysis and core server)
https://sftp.dequecloud.com/?u=SgNG&p=y72f&path=/comply.linux-6.1.4.run

2) mongo.conf (core server)
change bindIP to listen on 0.0.0.0
change dbPath....Note If you change this, be sure to make the directory
Changed default port from 27017 to 270178

3) redis.conf change bind value to IP or 0.0.0.0. (core server)

4) RabbitMQ  (core server)
enable plugins: rabbitmq-plugins enable rabbitmq_management
rabbitmqctl add_user {username} {password} && rabbitmqctl set_user_tags {username} administrator && rabbitmqctl set_permissions -p / {username} ".*" ".*" ".*"

5) Chrome vs firefox (install chrome on the analysis server)
1.) Import the public key used by the package management system: wget -q -O - https://dl-ssl.google.com/linux/linux_signing_key.pub | sudo apt-key add -
2.) Create the list file for RabbitMQ: echo "deb [arch=amd64] http://dl.google.com/linux/chrome/deb/ stable main" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/google-chrome.list
3.) Reload the local package database: sudo apt-get update
4.) Install the Google Chrome packages: sudo apt-get install -y google-chrome-stable

6) xvfb & GTk3 (core & analysis servers)
apt-get update
apt-get install -y libgtk-3-dev xvfb

7 set up the database cd /appdata/deque/bin/
./db_upgrade.sh

8. cd /appdata/deque/components/keycloak/standalone/configuration
vi standalone.xml
change <connection-url> to localhost </connection-url>


9. cd /appdata/deque/components/bin
./firstrun.sh (only run on new installs)

CTRL+C to kill the script
this script creates tables and users in the auth database. It is only necessary to run once during the install.


10. cd /appdata/deque/mounts/config-server/worldspace-core/production/
vi application.yml file
This is the database connection string. change the jdbc hostname line to 'localhost'

11. cd /appdata/deque/mounts/nginx/conf.d
vi comply.conf

in the serverline remove http://

restart nginx

12. chown worldspace:worldspace /appdata/deque -R


on the core server:
13. supervisorctl status
14. supervisorctl stop all
15. supervisorctl start scan-manager:ecp-registry & tail /appdata/deque/logs/registry.log
16. supervisorctl start scan-manager:ecp-config-server & tail /appdata/deque/logs/config-server.log
17. supervisorctl start scan-manager: & tail /appdata/deque/logs/custom-rules.log
18. supervisorctl start worldspace: & tail /appdata/deque/logs/keycloak.log
19. tail worldspace-core.log


on the analysis server
supervisorctl status
supervisorctl stop all
supervisorctl start scan-worker:

20. cd /appdata/deque/supervisord/ (on the analysis server)
vi comply.conf
--change autostart to false for the following: program:ecp-registry, and ecp-config-server----

[program:ecp-registry]
command=/appdata/deque/components/java/bin/java -jar /appdata/deque/components/comply/wars/registry-1.1.3.war -Xmx1024m -Xms256m -Djava.security.egd=file:/dev/./urandom --spring.profiles.active=production -XX:+ExitOnOutOfMemoryError
directory=/appdata/deque
autostart=false

[program:ecp-config-server]
command=/appdata/deque/components/java/bin/java -jar /appdata/deque/components/comply/wars/config-server-1.1.3.war  -Xmx1024m -Xms256m -Djava.security.egd=file:/dev/./urandom --eureka.client.serviceUrl.defaultZone=http://hhs-deque-core-01.stg.hhs.local:8761/eureka --spring.profiles.active=native -XX:+ExitOnOutOfMemoryError
directory=/appdata/deque
autostart=false

21. supervisorctl start scan-worker: (on the analysis server)
22. tail -f /appdata/deque/logs/worker.log (and make sure there are no errors in the log)

23. UI Work
- load the core server in a browser (hhs-deque-core-01.stg.hhs.local/auth)
default user/password is admin/admin

go to Clients
go to Comply

in the Valid reirects URIs
remove anything with worlspace-core, localhost, 127., etc. should only have 2 urls with stage-deque1.cloud.hhs.gov, and then add URLs for FQDN of the core server(eg: http://hhs-deque-core-01.stg.hhs.local/*  and https://hhs-deque-core-01.stg.hhs.local/*)



===================
Troubleshooting why the DNS doens't load. Suspect something with the Apache reverse proxy but configuration works in prod 
===================
/appdata/deque/mounts/config-server/realm/worldspace-comply/master
change keycloak.json DNS to FQDN of the server

/appdata/deque/mounts/config-server/worldspace-core/production/
change application.yml DNS to FQDN of the server
feServerBaseUrl: http://hhs-deque-core-01.stg.hhs.local/worldspace

*** NOTE: Do not start the worldspace comply service until the config-server service has fully started


24. in the UI: log in with admin@deque.com, admin. 
go to system settings
go to organizations
create a test Organization

====================================================================================
troubleshooting nginx

/appdata/deque/mounts/config-server/worldspace-core/production/
vi application.xml
scroll to the bottom and change http://stage-deque1.cloud.hhs.gov to http://FQDN of the server
which didn't work
so we changed this line from 80 to 443 (ie https://stage-deque1.cloud.hhs.gov)


Add'l troubleshooting after creating organization and creating a scan

vi /appdata/deque/mounts/config-server/worldspace-core/production/application.yml

====================================================================================


25. loading a database from backup

- supervisorctl stop all
- load the database (mysql import)


26. run db_upgrade.sh (only necessary on first install or reload of database)

27. start registry
28. start ecp-config-server
29. start scan-manager:
30. cat custom-rules.log make sure this starts before you start worldspace comply service
31. start worldspace:
32. on the analysis server: start the services


=================================================================================================================
# Some notes from the 6.1.4 upgrade
=================================================================================================================


For upgrades only
- stop all services
     supervisorctl stop all
- Analysis server: mkdir /etc/nginx/conf.d/
- back up directories
  Core Server only:
    /appdata/deque/components/keycloak/standalone/configuration
    /appdata/deque/mounts/
    /appdata/deque/properties/
- uninstall worldspace
   /appdata/deque/uninstall
   Remove remaining directories
- clean out the application directories
- reinstall
  Enter 21 times
  Core & Analysis servers
  - Analysis server does not require database information (insert null data in the prompts)
  - Analysis server: confirm symlink exists in /etc/supervisor/conf.d -> /appdata/deque/supervisord/comply.conf; supervisorctl reread; supervisorctl update
 chown worldspace:worldspace /appdata/deque -R
- restart nginx after step 3 (post installation steps)
- ** do not run first_run **
- Redis/mongo hardening
- confirm chrome version is 2.30

Deque 6.0 Notes

The following packages are required for 6.0 (Previously not required):
- rabbitmq 3.6.10-1
curl http://www.rabbitmq.com/rabbitmq-signing-key-public.asc | sudo apt-key add -
apt-get update
apt-get install rabbitmq-server
rabbitmq-plugins enable rabbitmq_management
chmod 664 enabled_plugins
service rabbitmq-server restart


rabbitmqctl adduser deque deque
rabbitmqctl adduser dqadmin admin
rabbitmqctl set_permissions -p / dqadmin ".*" ".*" ".*"

- Redis 3.2.9
apt-get install redid-server
- Nginx 1.4.6 (already installed)

- supervisor
pip install -U pip setuptools
easy_install supervisor
apt-get install supervisor
- xvfb
apt-get -y install xvfb
- chrome
wget -q -O - https://dl-ssl.google.com/linux/linux_signing_key.pub | sudo apt-key add - 
sudo sh -c 'echo "deb [arch=amd64] http://dl.google.com/linux/chrome/deb/ stable main" >> /etc/apt/sources.list.d/google-chrome.list'
sudo apt-get update 
sudo apt-get install google-chrome-stable
- mongo
sudo apt-key adv --keyserver hkp://keyserver.ubuntu.com:80 --recv 0C49F3730359A14518585931BC711F9BA15703C6
echo "deb [ arch=amd64 ] http://repo.mongodb.org/apt/ubuntu trusty/mongodb-org/3.4 multiverse" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/mongodb-org-3.4.list
apt-get update
apt-get install -y mongodb-org
- Additional required ports 
9100
- Deque support increased logging level (so far no impact to the system)
- Be sure to set up cron to clean up /tmp
- Install mysql
apt-get install mysql-server

- create wsauth and wscomply databases:
CREATE DATABASE `wsauth` /*!40100 DEFAULT CHARACTER SET latin1 */
CREATE DATABASE `wscomply` /*!40100 DEFAULT CHARACTER SET latin1 */

create wsdeque user:
create user ‘wsdeque’@’10.140.%.%’ identified by ‘password’;
grant all privileges on wsauth.* to 'wsdeque'@'10.140.%.%';
grant all privileges on wscomply.* to 'wsdeque'@'10.140.%.%';
flush privileges;





On the analysis server:
apt-get install -y supervisor

Create a file called /etc/supervisor/nginx.conf with the following:
[program:nginx]
command=/usr/sbin/nginx
autorestart=false






Starting the Deque services in version 6:
- Deque now uses supervisord to start services. To see what’s running, execute the following:
supervisorctl status
- The running services will be different for each server.




Here’s the core server:
***** Note nginx isn’t currently started by supervisor. this is a known issue. To start nginx, just do a start nginx
